<hr/>

<div class="container mt-3">
  <p class="mb-4">
    Ladies Let&apos;s Talk is a non-profit focused on connecting learners with volunteer partners for English practice and mentorship. 
    This project rebuilt the matching and tracking process from manual spreadsheets into an automated data pipeline and web-based workflow.
  </p>

  <div class="card mb-4">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="h5">Project Overview</h2>
      <p class="card-text">
        The organization previously relied on ad-hoc spreadsheets and manual matching, which did not scale as cohorts grew.
        I designed a structured data model and matching system that ingests learner and volunteer submissions, applies
        rule-based and score-based matching logic, and outputs clean match records that can be monitored over time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container mb-4">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap image-container">
